data.name: Subpoena
data.summary: The Subpoena IEPD was developed for the California Department of Justice - Data Exchange Project.
data.description: A Subpoena is a command to appear before a designated court on a particular date and time as a witness in a criminal action prosecuted by The People of The State of California.  A subpeona is sent from the Prosecutor and/or Public Defender to a Law Enforcement Agency and/or Sheriff's Department.  The Subpoenat contains court information such as court location, date, time, and signature block.  The Subpoena is one of 44 IEPDs developed by California Department of Justice - Data Exchange Project to support information exchange between state and local government organizations throughout the state of California.  It could also be adapted for use in other states.
